lead_paragraph: ADMIRAL HALSEY'S HEADQUARTERS IN THE SOUTH PACIFIC, Monday, Nov. 1 -- American forces are fighting a sharp engagement with the Japanese midway between the landing spot at Voza, on Choiseul Island, and the Japanese barge depot at Sangagai, which has been reinforced.
abstract: Solomon Islands: US forces clash with Jap troops between Voza and Sangagai, Choiseul; Jap fliers fail in effort to harass Allies by night raids; Allies balk Jap attempt to reinforce Choiseul or Treasury Islands; strafe Tonolei Harbor, Bougainville; fire 4 Jap cargo ships; scout planes attack Jap destroyers, Planet Harbor, Munda; damage 2; Allies raid Kara airdrome, Buin
